{"key":"processedPost-11520807","value":{"id":11520807,"first":11520092,"last":11520807,"when":1259110474,"utime":"11/25/09 02:54 AM","cleanedPost":"The soak helps to germinate some of the bacterial endospores, making them easier to kill in the pressure cooker.&nbsp; In my opinion, it's equally important for hydrating the grains slowly.&nbsp; If you put dry grains into water and boil or PC, you'll end up with a lot of burst kernels.&nbsp; In the old days, we added dry grains, a pinch of gypsum, and water to jars and then PCd it like that.&nbsp; It was much faster, but we also had a lot of burst kernels and higher rates of bacterial contamination then we do now following more modern procedures.<br />RR"}}